doubao-input (1.0.2-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Logo: replaced white-backed assets with transparent-background
    versions.  Previous logo.png / logo-128.png were RGBA but
    every corner pixel had alpha=255 (opaque white), which made
    the launcher icon look like a square badge and the README
    image show a white frame around the avatar.  The new avatar
    (697×736 RGBA, corners alpha=0) is genuinely transparent so
    the hicolor launcher badge blends with the desktop background
    and the README image sits flush on the page.

 -- doubao-input contributors <code-dream@qq.com>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 21:50:00 +0800

doubao-input (1.0.1-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * UI: PttOverlay rounded panel + breathing alpha + glint flash.
    - Rounded 18px corners via CSS provider.
    - Background alpha breathes 0.78~0.98 over 2.4s (opacity, not
      saturation — keeps wallpaper visible without eye strain).
    - Each new ASR word fires a 220ms opacity flash to 1.0 then
      400ms decay back to the breathing baseline.  Causal feedback
      makes the overlay feel alive without ever being noisy.
    - High-contrast white bold text is never animated, so reading
      stays stable while the edge glows.
  * UI: layout bug fixes
    - "你好" was wrapping to 2 lines (one char per line) — locked
      the label to a hard 360px width via set_size_request +
      set_width_chars(14) so Pango has a real break-width before
      the first size allocation.
    - Text appeared shifted right — box changed from HORIZONTAL
      to VERTICAL so the label is centered under the wave, not
      jammed against it.
    - "整行变 …" — removed set_ellipsize(START), which conflicts
      with wrap + max_width_chars + CJK WORD-wrap in GTK 4 /
      Pango and turns the whole line into a single ellipsis.
      Truncation is now handled in Python by text[-600:].
  * Packaging: .desktop Icon= uses absolute path to bypass
    GNOME Shell's per-session icon-theme cache.
  * Packaging: .deb installs wrapper, systemd user service, logo
    to hicolor theme, and postinst bootstraps a per-user venv
    with pure-Python deps (websockets, sounddevice, evdev).

 -- doubao-input contributors <code-dream@qq.com>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 21:05:00 +0800

